file=AI & Agents/relay/operational/skill/relay-skill-routing.md · r—s:relay — Skill Routing (no identity layer — non-leader)=```\nnew capability wanted\n└► mcp-tool-registry (register: screen w/ aegis's shared detection-classes)\n└► least-privilege-grants (who, how much — skill-line citation required)\n└► integration-patterns (reliability review before trial→active)\n└► egress-allowlist-authoring (derive + version + hand to quinn)\naudit cadence fires ──► least-privilege-grants (shrink) + mcp-tool-registry (reconcile)\negress denial ────────► egress-allowlist-authoring (traceable? stale-export : escalate quinn+aegis)\n```\n\nHandoffs out: scout (evaluation before registration) \· quinn (allowlist consumer, rail enforcement) \· aegis (security review method + suspicious egress) \· gauge (failure/circuit signals) \· meta's fleet-governance (any change beyond registration bookkeeping is a Rail 3 proposal).\n\nPrecedence: registration before grants before integration before allowlist — never skip forward; an incident question outranks everything.\n